This paper deals with machine learning models and fairness, which are topics that are commonly found in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer ethics (cs.CE). The paper also discusses regularizations and loss minimization, which are relevant to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CR). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on real-world datasets, which is a common feature of the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
